data.content:
## What breaks in .NET 11

**EF Core 11 fully removes sync I/O for the Cosmos DB provider.** In .NET 10 you could opt in to sync-over-async; in .NET 11 that opt-in is gone. Every synchronous call **always throws** — no workaround.

Your affected methods and their fixes:

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.ToListAsync();       // was ToList()
    }

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        return await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id); // was First()
    }

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.CountAsync();        // was Count()
    }

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();                  // was SaveChanges()
    }
}
```

**Key points:**
- `ToList()` → `await ToListAsync()`
- `First()` → `await FirstAsync()`
- `Count()` → `await CountAsync()`
- `SaveChanges()` → `await SaveChangesAsync()`
- All callers up the chain must also become `async`/`await`

This is a **medium-impact** change tracked at [dotnet/efcore#37059](https://github.com/dotnet/efcore/issues/37059).
